### Interactive API Tests
### Tests for InteractiveController endpoints
### Self-contained: creates a session first for permissions/respond, then cleans up.
### Run requests top-to-bottom.

### 1. Create session (captures sessionId)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sessions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "agent": "opencode"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("sessionId", response.body.id);
  client.log("Created session: " + response.body.id);
%}

### 2. Get pending questions
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/interactive/questions
Content-Type: application/json

> {%
  client.assert(response.status === 200, "Questions should return 200");
  client.log("Questions count: " + response.body.length);
%}

### 3. Reply to a question (requestId is @RequestParam, not in body)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/interactive/questions/reply?requestId=req_123
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "response": "Yes, proceed with the operation"
}

> {%
  client.log("Question reply response: " + response.status);
%}

### 4. Get pending permissions
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/interactive/permissions
Content-Type: application/json

> {%
  client.assert(response.status === 200, "Permissions should return 200");
  client.log("Permissions count: " + response.body.length);
%}

### 5. Reply to a permission request (requestId is @RequestParam, not in body)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/interactive/permissions/reply?requestId=perm_123
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "allow": true,
  "remember": false
}

> {%
  client.log("Permission reply response: " + response.status);
%}

### 6. Respond to a permission (sessionId + permissionId are @RequestParam, not in body)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/interactive/permissions/respond?sessionId={{sessionId}}&permissionId=perm_456
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action": "allow"
}

> {%
  client.log("Permission respond response: " + response.status);
%}

### 7. Deny a permission request
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/interactive/permissions/respond?sessionId={{sessionId}}&permissionId=perm_789
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action": "deny"
}

> {%
  client.log("Permission deny response: " + response.status);
%}

### 8. Delete session (cleanup)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/sessions/{{sessionId}}
Content-Type: application/json

> {%
  client.assert(response.status === 204, "Delete should return 204");
  client.log("Session deleted: " + client.global.get("sessionId"));
  client.global.set("sessionId", "");
%}
